title_full:
Angel Bat Dawid

              —
              The Oracle
            
              (International Anthem)
label: International Anthem
description: Angel Bat Dawid is an enigma; her debut album 'The Oracle’ (released earlier this year on tape) is a total anomaly. Dawid recorded, overdubbed and mixed the album on her own after a brain tumor diagnosis disrupted her music studies, she plays every instrument you hear (except for some drums), appears on the cover and produced every flawless twist and turn... more

label: PAN
description:
High-minded noise operatics and ruptured spoken word experiments from PAN mainstay Pan Daijing on her second album for the label. 

If Daijing's PAN debut "Lack" was operatic body horror, all fireworks and theatrics, "Jade" drags that body inside, dumps it into a grimy bathtub and locks the door. It's an anxious, solitary album that twins basement noise... more
